data.title: Why are iPhone 15’s different in price from most countries? - Quora
data.content: Why are iPhone 15’s different in price from most countries? - Quora Something went wrong. Wait a moment and try again. Try again Skip to content Skip to search Sign In Why are iPhone 15’s different in price from most countries? All related (31) Sort Recommended Vaughn Cordero Developer/Tinkerer, plumbs the depths of macOS and iOS · Author has 7K answers and 7.3M answer views · 1y The price analysis is based on USD and generally converted using an exchange rate thats projected to cover any currency volatility: in other words, a ‘cushion.’ Adjustments may be proposed by regional sales offices for weak market conditions, but Apple seldom if ever does the latter, but I don’t grab a spreadsheet to see if affluent economies get dinged disproportionately. Another factor is some countries require pricing to reflect national taxes like VAT, whereas others such as the US are given without sales taxes. So this can skew perception as well. Download 5.2K 5.2K Related questions More answers below Why are the iPhone prices different in different countries? Can you share the price of an iPhone 15 Pro in a different country? What are some differences in buying iPhones in different countries? What is the price of mobile after iPhone 15? What factors contribute to the varying prices of Apple iPhones in different countries? Jitendra Gehlot Adminstrative Assistant at Life Insurance Corporation of India (LIC) · Author has 455 answers and 4M answer views · 1y Related Can you share the price of an iPhone 15 Pro in a different country? Here is the Cost of an iPhone 15 Pro across Apple's top 5 markets. 1. US - ₹83,252/- 2. China - ₹93,850/- 3. Japan - ₹86,007/- 4. UK - ₹1,02,906/- 5. India - ₹1,34... Upvote · Kussh Aggarwal Tech Solution · Author has 384 answers and 1.2M answer views · 1y Related Why is the iPhone 15 series still priced more in India despite the fact that these devices are being manufactured in India? They are priced more, and still more expensive to purchase in India, but not because Apple chose to do so. No, this is not the ‘custom duty’ excuse. You have to know, the pricing in the US is listed before per-state sales tax is applied, meaning the price in US doesn't actually include taxes. Pricing in India is inclusive of 18% GST. Pricing in the US is before any tax. If we take a US priced iPhone 15 or 15 Plus, which cost $799 and $899 respectively, convert them into INR (1 USD = 82.96 INR as of writing this answer) which would be ₹66,284 and ₹74,580 respectively, and then add 18% GST which wo Continue Reading They are priced more, and still more expensive to purchase in India, but not because Apple chose to do so. No, this is not the ‘custom duty’ excuse. You have to know, the pricing in the US is listed before per-state sales tax is applied, meaning the price in US doesn't actually include taxes. Pricing in India is inclusive of 18% GST. Pricing in the US is before any tax. If we take a US priced iPhone 15 or 15 Plus, which cost $799 and $899 respectively, convert them into INR (1 USD = 82.96 INR as of writing this answer) which would be ₹66,284 and ₹74,580 respectively, and then add 18% GST which would be added on top of this base pricing, it comes to ₹78,215 and ₹88,004, which is not shy of Indian pricing of ₹79,900 for iPhone 15 and ₹89,900 for iPhone 15 Plus. See, it's not more expensive in India. It looks like it is, but US pricing is before tax and Indian pricing is after tax. However , you have to pay 18% in India in the form of GST and only upto 9.5% in the USA in the form of Sales tax which is different for different states of the US. This will make it slightly more expensive in India if you can’t avail GST set-off, but only by a smaller amount compared to before or compared to the pro models. The base price before GST in India for iPhone 15 would be ₹67,711 ($816, $17 more than the US pricing) and for iPhone 15 Plus it would be ₹76,186 ($918, $19 more than the US pricing). This small difference is understandable because of currency differences and how rupee is depreciating against dollar, and also 79,900 is for better looking as compared to ₹78,215 etc. iPhone 15 Pro and 15 Pro Max are still imported and include the custom duties, so they are much expensive than US models. Hope this helped clear your confusion, please consider upvoting, thanks! Upvote · 9 2 9 2 Costureiro Costura 6y Related Why are Apple products more expensive in other countries than in the US? Maybe because it has more taxes or more inflation in other country. I.e. where I live, in Brazil, we have to pay U$4049(exchanges taxes included) to buy a Macbook Pro 13″ 256gb SSD 8GB RAM i5 8gen.
